HTMLFencedFrameElementHeight.summary: NOTE Experimental The height property of the gets and sets the value of the corresponding {{htmlelement("fencedframe")}} height attribute, which specifies the height of the element.

remarks.para: The size of the embedded content may be set by internal contentWidth and contentHeight properties of the <fencedframe>'s object. In such cases, changing the or height of the <fencedframe> will change the size of the embedded container on the page, but the document inside the container will be visually scaled to fit. The reported width and height of the embedded document (i.e. and ) will be unchanged.

-Fenced frames on developers.google.com
-The Privacy Sandbox on developers.google.com

HTMLFencedFrameElementHeight.value: A string representing the height of the element in CSS pixels. The default value is 150.
